Alternatively (slightly DRY-er, one ThemeProvider wrapping both branches) — since the early-return pattern means two separate `return` statements, wrapping at the top of the function body is cleaner. This is the preferred approach: lift the `ThemeProvider` to wrap both return paths by restructuring to a single return:

```tsx
function RootRouteView() {
  const inner = !readNativeApi() ? (
    <div className="flex h-screen flex-col bg-background text-foreground">
      <div className="flex flex-1 items-center justify-center">
        <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          Connecting to {APP_DISPLAY_NAME} server...
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
