# Plan: Custom Theme System for T3 Code

## Context

The app currently has a minimal light/dark/system toggle (`hooks/useTheme.ts`, stored at `t3code:theme`) that drives a single `.dark` class on `<html>`. The task replaces this with a proper multi-theme system: three built-in named themes ("t3-dark", "t3-light", "t3-midnight"), each with a complete color palette, a React Context provider, localStorage persistence, and a visual theme selector with preview swatches.

No new dependencies. No build config changes.

---

## Files to Create

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` | Types + built-in theme definitions |
| `apps/web/src/components/ThemeProvider.tsx` | Module store + React Context + `useTheme` hook |
| `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` | Swatch-based selector component |

## Files to Modify

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `packages/shared/package.json` | Add `./theme` subpath export |
| `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` | Replace with thin re-export shim |
| `apps/web/src/index.css` | Append three `[data-theme]` palette blocks |
| `apps/web/src/routes/__root.tsx` | Wrap tree with `<ThemeProvider>` |
| `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` | Replace Appearance section |

---

## Step 1 — `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` (new)

Pure TypeScript data module. No Effect/Schema needed. No side effects. Works in browser and server.

```typescript
export type ThemeId = "t3-dark" | "t3-light" | "t3-midnight";

export interface ThemeColors {
  readonly background: string;
  readonly foreground: string;
  readonly accent: string;
